1. Pre-Engagement
      Create all the necessary documents in the pre-engagement phase, discuss the assessment objectives, and clarify any questions.
2. Information Gathering
      Investigate the company's existing website we have been assigned to assess. We identify the technologies in use and learn how the web application functions.
3. Vulnerability Assessment
      Look for known vulnerabilities and investigate questionable features that may allow for unintended actions.
4. Exploitation
      Prepare our exploit code, tools, and environment and test the webserver for these potential vulnerabilities.
5. Post-Exploitation
      Jump into information gathering and examine the webserver from the inside. If we find sensitive information during this stage, we try to escalate our privileges (depending on the system and configurations).
6. Lateral Movement
      Move through the network and access other hosts and servers using the information we have gathered.
7. Proof-of-Concept
      Create a proof-of-concept that proves that these vulnerabilities exist and potentially even automate the individual steps that trigger these vulnerabilities.
8. Post-Engagement
      Documentation is completed and presented to our client as a formal report deliverable. Afterward, we may hold a report walkthrough meeting to clarify anything about our testing or results and provide any needed support to personnel tasked with remediating our findings.
